ed the development of our colleges and universities ever since. He shows how Robert's rules can help faculty, administrators, and students to solve problems and overcome challenges through collaboration, disciplined thinking, trust in the facts, and honesty and fairness from all sides.At a time when people's faith in democracy and higher education has been shaken to its core, Robert's Rules of Order offers a powerful reminder of the importance of democratic norms and practices in American life and institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDemocracy and educationzUnited States. 0aParliamentary practicezUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / Reference.2bisacsh1 aLoss, Christopher P., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishz978311075406308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2021z978311075395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073912140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691222851zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691222851423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691222851/original  a978-3-11-073912-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075395-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075406-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishb2021  aEB